---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Me from "../images/me.jpeg";
const title = "About me";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={title}>
  <div class="grid prose">
    <PageHeader heading={title}>Get to know me a bit better</PageHeader>
  </div>
  <div class="grid prose">
    <Image
      src={Me}
      alt="Portrait photo of Hans Sandberg, looking straight at the camera and smiling while sitting outside at a restaurant."
    />
    <p>
      I’ve always been fascinated by the intersection of psychology, technology,
      and design. This curiosity led me to study psychology. First
      neuropsychology, because I was captivated by how the brain works, and
      later applied cognitive psychology, where I learned how scientific
      insights about human thought and behaviour can be applied in practical
      settings.
    </p>
    <p>
      During that second master’s, a course on human-computer interaction opened
      my eyes to UX as a career. I realised it was possible to combine
      psychology, tech, and design into a single profession and I was hooked. An
      internship at a UX research consultancy gave me a hands-on introduction to
      usability testing and user research, but I quickly discovered I wanted to
      do more than evaluate interfaces. I wanted to design them.
    </p>
    <p>
      This led me to a post-master in user-system interaction, where I learned
      the principles of user-centred design and earned a professional doctorate
      in engineering. My first role as a UX designer marked the start of my
      career, and over the years the technology side has grown increasingly
      central. Learning front-end development allowed me to bridge the gap
      between design and code.
    </p>
    <p>
      Today, I work as a product designer and help create products that balance
      user needs, business goals, and technical realities. My background allows
      me to move comfortably between research, design, and implementation,
      collaborating closely with product and engineering throughout the process.
      I’m driven by the belief that the best products come from understanding
      people, solving real problems, and sweating the details.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
